package demo;

public class Customer {
	private int custNo; 		
	private String custName;
	private String custAddr; 
	void init(){
		custNo=1;
		custName="Ram";
		custAddr="Chennai";
	}
	public void display1() {
		System.out.println("custNo: "+custNo+"\ncustName: "+custName+"\ncustAddr: "+custAddr);
	}
}


Create an object of Customer 

Use init() for initializing an object of Customer  

Use display() for displaying details of Customer. 

 

Setters and getters: 

 

Modify above assignment and define setters and getters methods to initialize or set individual  

variables. Call them from main methods of PizzaHut class. 